                "7. One of the twelve volunteered to scan for a clue. \"Pass me the ticket I will check for it in the Holy Spirit\". He was immediately entranced by the Holy Spirit, but gave up after a while. Each of the twelve took turns to draw on their visionary powers but none was able to complete the puzzle. The letter remained, a riddle unsolved.",
                "8. After a while I asked for my ticket, \"Give it back, please will you\". I too soared into the trance of the Holy Spirit to have the divine power make me utter the word \"**UNKNOWN**\". I said, \"You see now, that is indeed my name. '**UNKNOWN**' meaning that I or my angel are not known yet or easily to anyone. Now, you will recall what our Lord Jesus Christ said to his disciples the other day. \"There is one among you whom you do not know?\" This vision or revelation built a firm confidence in me, making me more than convinced that the African Apostolic Church was to benefit from the participation of the twelve apostles from the team of the Holy Lamb, Jesus.",
